metadata.name: Interdependency #103
metadata.description:
"Interdependency" is the third collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

Established systems are fragile. All elements of the system depend on each other, and at the same time allow all others to exist. What happens if one element disappears? The beautiful, harmonic, established system completely refuses to function, it shatters into tiny pieces. It's unrecoverable. It's gone. Probably forever.

metadata.name: impressions 04 #443
metadata.description:
The final of four impressions, an exercise in pulling discernible patterns from utter chaos. 

Palette - One of 10 different color palettes.
Shape - Is the source an ellipse or a square?
Divisions - The X/Y resolution of the pattern.
xRand & yRand - the X and Y dimensions of each element.

metadata.name: intersection 2 #71
metadata.description:
The final entry in my "vintage CG" tetraptych (which comprises "intersection," "reflection," "reflection 2," and this piece), "intersection 2" revisits the motivation for "intersection," and combines it with the stipple drawing of "reflection." Essentially, it is the derived essence of the previous three pieces, and the four together make a contiguous view of the original idea. If one desired a collection goal, one could match the palettes in a pleasing combination, or collect one from each where the Quantity trait was the same. (Or whatever. You do you!) 

Created in p5.js. Happy holidays and best wishes to all!

metadata.name: Resilience  #120
metadata.description:
Resilience is a collection of endless architectures.
In a resilient generative system composed of multiple compatible parts, real-time information exchange enables open reconfigurations and continuous discrete adjustments. Sometimes vague and fuzzy, sometimes real and tangible, they reveal different readings of architectural complexity and scale: from city plans to floor plans and details to sections and elevations.

Resilience comes in a variety of polychrome palettes, ascii glyphs, and styles. 
To enjoy it in full-screen mode, press the left mouse button in live mode, for a monochrome look press 'b'. Made with P5js.

Resilience Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022

metadata.name: Refractions #261
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective
